    <refsection id="Description_CMTC_ActuatedPulley">
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>
            This block is a model of an actuated Pulley (without mass and inertia, geometric constraint). If F_flange_b1 and F_flange_b2
            are the forces applied to the translational driving flanges and F_flange_a is the one applied to the flange at center of pulley, we have:
        </para>
        <para>
            F_flange_b1 = F_flange_b2 + force, with force = torque_axle/r
        </para>
        <para>
            and F_flange_a + F_flange_b1 + F_flange_b2 =0
        </para> 
    </refsection>
